node.text: ¬©Ô∏èDanny Luna Photography.  As Mike Tyson put it “Everyone has a plan until they get punched.” ü•ä Right now it feels like the whole world has been punched in the face and is looking stunned as to what to do next. Garlic Shrimp Tacos Ingredients:
üì∏: @spacelyyy 
2lbs Shrimp, deshelled and deveined 
1 tablespoon Old Bay Seasoning 
¬Ω teaspoon Cajun Seasoning 
¬Ω teaspoon Black Pepper 
1 tablespoon Garlic Powder 
1 tablespoon Onion Powder 
3 Garlic Cloves Pressed or Minced 
2 cups Shredded Mexican Cheese 
Fresh Cilantro 
Yellow Onions 
Cherry Tomatoes, diced 
Olive Oil 
Canola Oil [ For Crispy Tortillas ] 
Avocado [ Optional ] 
Sourcream [ Optional ] 
Limes 
Lettuce [ You can use any kind of lettuce but, I used Boston Lettuce ] 
White Corn Tortillas 
First, in a large bowl season the shrimp with black pepper, Old Bay seasoning, cajun seasoning, garlic powder, onion powder, then squeeze in some lime juice. Give it a good stir. Then set aside to marinate for 20 minutes. 
Next, preheat the olive oil for frying. Chop the onions and garlic and then place them in the oil for frying until tender. Add the shrimp to the hot pan and saute for 10 minutes, flipping occasionally, until the shrimp are cooked through.

ICE AGE. 
Available Now - A spectacular Victorian silver-plated Arctic themed table centrepiece with frosted glass dish, the base cast to represent a glacial backround to the creatures formed as part of the stand: polar bear and walrus.
Registered design mark for 29th March, 1876.
Designed and made at the time of the British Arctic Expedition of 1875-1876.

Early voyages to the Arctic were as hazardous as voyages to the Moon and captured the popular imagination as space travel does today.

THE BRITISH ARCTIC EXPEDITION OF 1875-1876.
It had been 30 years since the last British expedition to the Arctic (under John Franklin, which lost every single member of its crew) when Sir George Nares was sent by the British Admiralty to attempt to reach the North Pole via Smith Sound.

Two ships, HMS Alert and HMS Discovery sailed from Portsmouth on 29th May 1875; about 200,000 people turned up to wave them off. The British public hoped they would be the first vessels to reach the North Pole.

However, the crews suffered from scurvy (vitamin C deficiency) with four deaths, snow blindness and exhaustion. This and impenetrable ice prevented them from reaching the North Pole.
None the less, the expedition reached the highest northern latitude so far for a ship and a sledging party.

The expedition returned to the UK in the Autumn of 1876 and were well rewarded and Nares was knighted. The geology of Northern Canada and Greenland is littered with the names of those connected with the 1875-1876 Expedition.

node.text:
We've been away for a hot minute. Like many, we've been digesting everything that's been happening in the world and trying to make sense of where we find ourselves. Who saw this as our 2020?  We've been grieving on many levels, personally and across borders. We've become angry, motivated, active and united in ways we never have before. The Black Lives Matter Movement has been at the centre of this. People of all colours are beginning to do the work to understand what it means to be actively anti-racist. People are beginning to step into their responsibility and vulnerability. 

Our self care and collective wellness is more important than ever. It got us thinking about safe spaces; spaces that nourish, affirm and celebrate us as black and brown people. Where are these spaces? What do they look like? How can we create more of them?

Enter, Notting Hill Carnival! If this isn't a space that celebrates black and brown people we don't know what is?! 

As we make it a point to explore more safe spaces, join us as we take part in our first Notting Hill Carnival across the inter-webs. We'll be dropping the tea on getting carnival ready tomorrow.

Ama & Leila
X

node.text: Hiking Venture Day 3 (Part Two). That first photo says it all. Accomplishment. Victory. We did it. We conquered Knife's Edge. And with Mount Adams in sight, we headed towards a water source and camp. The last night was the only night we didn't have to scramble to set up camp in the rain. Chili and mozzarella sticks rolled in bread was an amazing way to end the day. The crescent moon peeked through the trees and the stars came out in a bold fashion. What a day.
